Overview: 

If you're looking for the stability of a profitable, growing company with the entrepreneurial spirit of a startup, we’re hiring. SageSure , a leader in catastrophe-exposed property insurance, is seeking a  Program Solutions Engineer  . SageSure is seeking an individual to oversee the technical analysis, development, user acceptance testing (UAT) and delivery of strategic projects. The Program Solutions Analyst role will develop a breadth of subject-matter expertise on topics which include SageSure’s insurance products, operations, and user experience. The ideal candidate will have strong communication and collaboration skills, coupled with a demonstrated executive presence.

 What you’d be doing: 

 Collaborate on the implementation of new insurance programs, portfolios, or product launches using SageSure’s technology ecosystem.  Understand the intricacies of the insurance program technology ecosystem and conduct technical impact analysis of new program launches.  Identify opportunities for improvement in product authoring tools and assist in automation enhancements.  Collaborate closely with software engineering and technical teams to ensure precise implementation of new portfolio additions.  Act as a cross-functional technical insurance product liaison, engaging with line of business owners and stakeholders from different disciplines and competencies.  Use critical thinking skills to deliver innovation and practical solutions to solve complex problems.  Communicate and navigate effectively with stakeholders from different disciplines and competencies with a demonstrated executive presence.  Uphold the established standard of excellence for quality and timely project delivery.  Prepare technical document including reference manuals and job aids  Ad hoc projects and responsibilities as assigned. 


 We’re looking for someone who has: 

 Bachelor's degree in business, actuarial, computer science, or related field.  Strong math aptitude and analytic thinking.  Advanced Excel competencies and experience with complex formulas and VBA.  Applied knowledge of SQL/TSQL/XML/HTML/JSON.  Detail-oriented and a structured thinker.  Enterprise mindset with a passion for improvement.  Ability to manage multiple tasks and competing deadlines while working independently.  Proficiency in written and oral communication skills.  Ability to create functional documentation. 


 Highly preferred candidates also have: 

 Previous experience in Property & Casualty insurance industry is preferred .  Applied knowledge of SQL/TSQL/XML/HTML/JSON.  Proficiency in one of the following programming languages: C#, C++, Python, R.  Proficiency in Visual Studio Code and GitLab.  Experience with workforce management software (JIRA).  Proficiency in data analytics tool Alteryx. 


About SageSure:

As a Best Places to Work in Insurance Recipient for four years in a row (2020-2023), SageSure, one of the largest residential property insurance managing general underwriter (MGU) in the United States, is pioneering ways people protect their American Dream.

A leader in catastrophe-exposed property insurance, SageSure was founded in 2009 to deliver reliable products, exceptional customer experiences, and strong underwriting results in challenging insurance markets. SageSure currently operates in 14 states and provides home, flood, and commercial coverage on behalf of its highly rated carrier partners.

We have more than 600 employees working remotely or hybrid in one of our eight offices—Jersey City, NJ; Mountain View, CA; Chicago, IL; Tallahassee, FL; Cincinnati, OH; Houston, TX; Mt. Laurel, NJ; and Cheshire, CT—who are tackling the industry’s toughest challenges.

We provide generous health benefits and perks, including tuition reimbursement, wellness allowance, paid volunteer time off, a matching 401K plan, and more.

SageSure is a proud Equal Opportunity Employer committed to building a workforce that reflects the spectrum of perspectives, experiences, and abilities of the world we live in. We recognize that our differences make us strong, and we actively seek out diverse candidates through partnerships with organizations, institutions and communities that represent various backgrounds. We champion belonging and inclusion for all identities, including, but not limited to, race, ethnicity, religion, sexual orientation, age, veteran status, ability status, gender, and country of origin, striving to create a culture where all individuals feel valued, respected, and empowered to bring their authentic selves to work.

Our nimble, highly responsive culture nurtures critical thinkers who run toward problems and engineer solutions. We relentlessly pursue better outcomes by investing in the technology, talent, and tools that position us to succeed in demanding markets. Come join our team! Visit sagesure.com/careers to find a position for you.

Job Description:

DXC Technology (NYSE: DXC) helps global companies run their mission critical systems and operations while modernizing IT, optimizing data architectures, and ensuring security and scalability across public, private and hybrid clouds. The world’s largest companies and public sector organizations trust DXC to deploy services across the Enterprise Technology Stack to drive new levels of performance, competitiveness, and customer experience. Learn more about how we deliver excellence for our customers and colleagues at DXC.com

Job Description:

The Associate Manager of Software Engineering is a highly skilled, self-driven servant leader with an immense understanding of DXC’s Property and Casualty and Claims Product Family offerings including application end-to-end processing, P&C industry knowledge, strong people management, delivery focus, and software development process expertise.

Serve as the liaison between the account teams, DXC project teams, and customers. Possess strong interpersonal and negotiation skills to build a solid value proposition and create a conducive win-win situation. Collaborate with multiple counterparts to deliver the release objectives, lead the release, and facilitate the adoption of value-added business solutions.

Essential Job Functions:

Work as the Product Manager for product offerings as assigned within the DXC P&C and Claims Product Families managing the end-to-end release milestones, ensuring seamless delivery, and understanding the customer community. Strong People, Process, Release Execution/Lifecycle, and product knowledge with focus and understanding of P&C and Claims domainSeamlessly create, manage, lead, and strategize the product roadmap by working closely with the Offering/Strategy Manager, Product Management Leader, Delivery Leaders, and counterpartsOversee the entire product development and modification life cycle process from inception through delivery phasesMonitor the overall release life cycle, project tracking & status reporting, process review, and compliance on pre-determined release parametersStaff projections, resource planning, and scheduling for the releaseManage offshore and domestic project team members to ensure communication and understanding of deadlines, assignments, and objectivesRelease budgeting / scope-of-work (SoW) negotiations to participate actively in the roadmap and investment discussionsReview proposed solutions, T-shirt size estimations, and ROM estimates for enhancements and negotiate the scopeEnsure the Product Development team adheres to the SAFe® Agile Development Methodology, perform perpetual reviews of project status, identify potential project risks, and recommend and implement risk mitigation solutions as appropriateWork with the build teams and product owners to create project definitions, schedules, and objectives for various features from small to large complexity. Prepare detailed SoW, release whitepaper and gain concurrence & approval from DXC-internal and external stakeholders regarding delivery aspects of the releaseActively participate in the delivery assurance reviews to ensure adherence to project management standards and proceduresClosely interact with the Delivery organization and technical/functional staff, understand their requirements, and propose solutions using specialized knowledge of DXC’s product offering, market and customer needs

Communication And Release Cadence:

Establish a seamless communication mechanism and networking conduit between Insurance Portfolio and Solution stakeholders encompassing multiple Agile Release Trains (ARTs) in diverse geographies, including DXC leadership and, most importantly, a wide array of existing/potential customer pursuits backed by solid Lean Business Case, Benefit Hypothesis, etcPivotal stakeholders in Planning Iteration release meetings, stakeholder review meetings, monthly cadences with the Delivery and Sales Leadership counterparts, etcFoster an inter- or intra-team conducive environment, discuss pain points/risks, brainstorm mitigation plans/solutions, and negotiate a timeline/schedule for the quarterly release(s) based on the committed DoD/WSJFFoster the overall release cadence based on the Product roadmap discussions, budgeting, scheduling, staff projections / Scope-of-Work (SoW), and frequently collaborate with multiple pockets across other teams, DXC Product Engineering, and Services organizationsSeamlessly supports the product strategy, actively determines the release milestones, whitepapers, and checklist reviews, and ensures seamless release deliveries to the customers

Budgeting And Financials:

Monitor the product release life cycle, tracking NRVs, process review, and compliance on pre-determined release parameters (including budget/time/scope). Billing and Staff projections, budget adherence, schedule compliance, resource planning, and scheduling for the releaseLeverage offshore and domestic project team members to ensure communication and understanding of deadlines, assignments, and objectivesPerform Contract and MESA licensing and renewals, billing/invoicing, procurement, vendor management, etcPrepare detailed SoW, release Whitepaper approval discussions with the Accounting/Finance team, and gain concurrence & approval from DXC-internal and external stakeholders regarding delivery aspects of the release. Actively participate in the delivery assurance reviews to ensure adherence to the project management standards, exit criteria, matrices, financial forecast (P&L), and other indices/parameters

Management And Administrative Functions:

Timesheet reviews and approvals Performance reviews Contract understanding Billing and Invoicing Vendor Management and s/w licensing/procurement Finance Procedures and Tracking Budgets (Forecasts/Actuals), WBS owner, etc.

Basic Qualifications:

Bachelor's degree or equivalent combination of education and experience Bachelor's degree in business administration, information systems (or) related field preferred Twelve (or) more years of relevant experience Experience working with the interface of information technology with functional groups within the organization. Proficient with Microsoft Office tools, SharePoint, Outlook, Teams, etc.

Other Skills:

 Strong verbal and written communication and leadership skills Strong negotiation, interpersonal and presentation skills Ability to lead and work in a fast-paced SAFE® Agile model comprising of multiple teams & geographies involving time overlaps Ability to handle multiple tasks simultaneously and switch between tasks seamlessly Willingness to travel, as required

Work Environment:

 Remote (or) Office environment, as required

Compensation at DXC is influenced by an array of factors, including but not limited to the experience, job-related knowledge, skills, competencies, as well as contract-specific affordability and organizational requirements. A reasonable estimate of the current compensation range for this position is $84,100 - $156,100.

Full-time hires are eligible to participate in the DXC benefit program. DXC offers a comprehensive, flexible, and competitive benefits program which includes, but is not limited to, health, dental, and vision insurance coverage; employee wellness; life and disability insurance; a retirement savings plan, paid holidays, paid time off.

Recruitment fraud is a scheme in which fictitious job opportunities are offered to job seekers typically through online services, such as false websites, or through unsolicited emails claiming to be from the company. These emails may request recipients to provide personal information or to make payments as part of their illegitimate recruiting process. DXC does not make offers of employment via social media networks and DXC never asks for any money or payments from applicants at any point in the recruitment process, nor ask a job seeker to purchase IT or other equipment on our behalf. More information on employment scams is available here.

Job Tittle - Senior Engineering ManagerJob Location -Reston, VAClient Summary -We are Consulting/Engineering firm founded in 1949 in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. Our main specialty is consulting and inspection in the protective coatings and construction industries.

Cobalt GP – acquired by FactSet in 2021 – is a portfolio monitoring tool. Cobalt is private capital’s key to collecting, analyzing, and reporting on fund and portfolio company financial metrics. Private equity and venture capital funds use Cobalt’s intuitive technology platform to gain important operational efficiencies, address complex LP and management demands, and competitively position their firm. Cobalt tailors its portfolio monitoring, investor relations, and benchmarking analysis tools according to our clients’ size and investment style to match their needs.

We're seeking an ambitious Associate Product Manager to join our team. This entry-level role offers a high degree of independence, inviting you to take initiative and ownership of product features. Perfect for a self-starter aiming to make a significant impact, this position is an open canvas for fresh contributions within a dynamic, fast-paced environment. If you're looking to launch and accelerate your product management career with a hands-on, highly collaborative experience, this role is your springboard.

Key Responsibilities:

Support the Product Manager in shaping the strategy and objectives for the Cobalt Portfolio Monitoring platform. Assume responsibility for specific elements of the product development cycle, gaining valuable hands-on experience. Generate innovative product concepts, supported by market research and client interactions, to continually refine our offerings. Work with clients and stakeholders to grasp their needs, translating insights into tangible product enhancements. Partner with cross-functional teams to align on product goals, driving feature implementation with precision and clarity. Engage in agile planning sessions and facilitate communication between technical teams, ensuring a cohesive approach to product delivery. Act as a point of contact for clients, honing your client-facing communication skills and collecting essential feedback. Contribute to product documentation and knowledge sharing within the team, leveraging tools like Confluence. Leverage user analytics tools, such as Heap, to drive data-informed decisions that shape the future direction of the platform. Perform detailed competitive analyses and remain current with industry trends, advocating for best-in-class product experiences. 

Requirements:

Bachelor’s degree - STEM, finance, economics, or another relevant field helpful but not required. 2-4 years' relevant experience. Possesses a product mindset—starts from problems, goals, and needs, and then experiments to uncover the best solution. Strong user interview and data collection skills; Adept at leveraging a range of tools and methods and inferring insights from data. Strong understanding of competitors and end-markets informs product strategy. Capable of inspiring a cross-functional team to deliver on the product strategy and vision. Ability to align and influence engineering, design, product marketing, and other stakeholders. Demonstrated autonomy and impact in previous roles. 

Cobalt is a highly collaborative environment. You will work closely with your product colleagues, design, engineering, QA, customer success, and sales. You will be part of a team that wants to hear your opinions, ideas and concerns. That means you need to be an emotionally intelligent, pragmatic and straightforward person who is comfortable sharing your thoughts and feedback.

This role is designed to evolve. With a commitment to mentoring and skills development, we will equip you to not only contribute to the product's success but also pave your path upwards within the product management field. Your drive and performance can open doors to greater responsibilities and leadership positions within our organization.

Job Title: Senior Software Engineer 

This position is hybrid - working 2 days a week in the Denton, Texas Support Center.

“At Sally Beauty Holdings, we find beauty in diversity. Our inclusivity and self-expression are what fuel our innovation and growth. You are welcome here, and you can thrive here. We find beauty in YOU. Join us.”

Essential Function

We are looking for an experienced Infrastructure Engineer to develop and manage infrastructure projects and processes. A passion to learn and try new things, keen attention to detail, problem-solving abilities, and solid knowledge base are essential. Strong verbal and written communication skills and able to multitask, prioritize, and manage time efficiently. Efficient with SQL codes/queries. Efficient with PowerShell and capacity to learn additional scripting tools. Knowledgeable with Azure Cloud and Oracle Cloud. Willing to go on-call if needed.

Knowledge, Skills And Abilities .

Bachelors degree in Computer Science or Computer Information Systems with 8+ years of relevant programming skills.Programming Language experience specific to the work group that this team member is a part of.Must have SQL Database KnowledgeExperience in SQL Series, Coding and QueriesAzure Cloud or similar platformVMwareKnowledge of Oracle Cloud a plus but not required3+ years of team leadership experience.


Primary Duties

60%: Writes new code or modifies existing code to meet requirements of company business applications. Tests or Debugs his/her work to ensure that the functional requirements are met and that completed work is of high quality. Follows company development standards which are particular to their team.

15%: Provides production support in the form of troubleshooting problems, break fixes, adhoc data mining or other unspecified activities as directed by management. May be on call for afterhours support.

10%: Performs review, analysis and design on new assignments identifying opportunities and challenges that may be signification to the successful completion of the assignment. Works with end users, Third Parties, other IT staff and management to define, plan and scope projects. Relies on experience and judgement to accomplish these goals.

10%: Occasionally leads or directs the work of others.

5%: Complies with existing documentation requirements required for the Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC). Complies with Payment Card Industry (PCI) requirements as required.

Working Conditions/ Physical Requirements

The work environment involves everyday risks or discomforts which require normal safety precautions typical of such places as offices, meeting and training rooms, retail stores, and residences or commercial vehicles, e.g., use of safe work practices with office equipment, avoidance of trips and falls, observance of fire regulations and traffic signals, etc. The work area is adequately lighted, heated, and ventilated.The work is sedentary. Typically, the employee may sit comfortably to do the work. However, there may be some walking; standing; bending; carrying of light items such as papers, files, books, small parts; using a keyboard, driving an automobile, etc.. No special physical demands are required to perform the work.


Competencies / Attributes 

Puts Customers FirstExcellent communication and customer service skills.Demonstrates AccountabilityTakes responsibility for performance and team relationships and always seeks to improve.Shows a Bias for ActionProactively researches and solves issues.Acts as OneStrong interpersonal skills and works great as part of a team.Aptitude for InnovationKeeps up with industry trends and knowledge.Builds TalentMentors and trains junior staff and shares knowledge.


Benefits

We offer a competitive salary and outstanding benefits package that includes medical, dental, vision, life Insurance, paid vacation and sick days, paid holidays, tuition reimbursement and 401(k) with company match. In addition, associates of SBH may take advantage of our in house salon with complementary services and a varied selection of food options at our corporate campus. Also, featured at our corporate campus, is both a Sally Beauty and CosmoProf Professional onsite store, where associates enjoy a great merchandise discount!

Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to their race, color, religion, national origin, sex, or disability.

Job Number: 24-01104

Use your skills where innovative technology solutions begin. Eclaro is looking for an Infrastructure Engineer for our client in Saint Cloud, MN. 

Eclaro’s client is a leading technology solutions provider, collaborating with customers to manage their needs and achieve success in their business goals. If you’re up to the challenge, then take a chance at this rewarding opportunity!

Responsibilities: 

Systems Management:Comprehensive knowledge of the Microsoft 365 portfolio, Microsoft server, virtualization technologies, SAN, firewall technologies, firewall security policies, NAT's and DMZ, network L2 / L3 configurations, VoIP telephony, SSO, Federation, Multifactor Authentication, backup and recovery technologies, and archiving strategies. Ensuring proper licensing is tracked and maintained within infrastructure, including but not limited to systems, servers, CAL's, firewalls, route / switch, endpoints, M365, telephony, MDM, and Infrastructure SaaS applications. Participate in evaluating existing and future technologies and makes recommendations for software and hardware upgrades. Participate in the design, implementation, administration, maintenance, capacity planning, and on-going life-cycle management of all infrastructure equipment, including the remote locations. Ensuring systems are properly monitored and stay within acceptable operating parameters and service levels, communicating outages and slowdowns to appropriate stakeholders. Maintaining system protocols, changes in architectures by documenting and updating changes & procedures. Collaborating with internal resources, consultants / contractors to optimize system performance. Participate in the evaluation of security logs and work with the Managed SOC on security incidents and infrastructure vulnerability management. Service Desk Management:Working with and being the conduit for all L3 / L4 escalated issues in a timely manner and managing request workflows and metrics. Coordinate and work with vendors to identify and resolve escalated issues. Provide technical mentoring and training for junior IT Operations team members. Communication:Providing status reports and metrics to include available capacity, project pipeline, and technical challenges to management to support business operations tactically and strategically. Ability to communicate in a positive and effective manner with management, end users, coworkers, and vendors. Change Control Management:Ensuring proper change control and notification procedures are followed to protect the stability and persistence of the production environment. Project Coordination:Drive planning, coordination, testing, implementation, and support of assigned projects relating to upgrades, repairs, and enhancements of the IT environment, including vendor coordination, telecommunications, network and storage infrastructure, endpoint and server, enterprise applications, etc. Communicate and develop consensus with customers on projects, challenges, proposed solutions, and system changes. 
Qualifications:

A minimum of 10 years' Technical Support experience in a small-to-medium sized company full-time experience supporting the following enterprise systems: M365, network, server, storage, IT security and telephony. A minimum of 5 years' experience managing enterprise infrastructure projects. Four-year College Diploma or University Degree in Computer Science or equivalent experience. Proven experience with systems planning, security principles, and general system management best practices.

At Blue Origin, we envision millions of people living and working in space for the benefit of Earth. We’re working to develop reusable, safe, and low-cost space vehicles and systems within a culture of safety, collaboration, and inclusion. Join our diverse team of problem solvers as we add new chapters to the history of spaceflight! 
Blue Origin Introduction
At Blue Origin, we envision millions of people living and working in space for the benefit of Earth. We’re working to develop reusable, safe, and low-cost space vehicles and systems within a culture of safety, collaboration, and inclusion. Join our diverse team of problem solvers as we add new chapters to the history of spaceflight! 
As part of a hardworking team of diverse engineers, you will develop flight software and tools for various spaceflight systems. You will share in the team’s impact on all aspects of safety-critical real-time embedded software development. Working in the Avionics Center of Excellence embedded software organization, you will be part of the world-class team responsible for creating the platform software that will enable all Business Units to carry people and payloads routinely to Earth orbit and beyond. You will work on vehicle avionics and be responsible for requirements, architecture, design, implementation, integration and testing of various software components and tools critical for the success of each program’s mission. If relocating to one of the approved Blue Origin sites, we offer relocation assistance!
We are looking for someone to apply their technical expertise, leadership skills, and commitment to quality to positively impact safe human spaceflight. Passion for our mission and vision is required!
Minimum Qualifications
B.S. degree in computer science, computer engineering, electrical engineering, or related discipline. Minimum 12 years of experience in low-level software development.Experience defining software architecture and design.Proficient in C, C++, and Python. Strong knowledge of embedded software, kernel development, BSPs or other systems software components. Good understanding of computer architecture, operating systems, and network protocols fundamentals.Strong written and verbal communication skills.Ability to earn trust, maintain positive and professional relationships, and contribute to a culture of inclusion. Must be a U.S. citizen or national, U.S. permanent resident (current Green Card holder), or lawfully admitted into the U.S. as a refugee or granted asylum. 
Preferred Qualifications
M.S. degree in computer science, computer engineering, electrical engineering, or related discipline. Experience with real-time operating systems. Experience with safety-critical software development in aerospace, automotive or other industries. Working knowledge of hardware components and programmable logic. 
Compensation range for on site WA applicants is $200,858-$281,200
Compensation range for on site CA applicants is $200,858-$281,200
Other Site Ranges May Differ
Inclusivity Statement
Don’t meet all desired requirements? Studies have shown that some people are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single desired qualification. At Blue Origin, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace, so if you’re excited about this role but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly with every desired qualification in the job description, we encourage you to apply anyway. You may be just the right candidate for this or other roles.
Export Control Regulations
Applicants for employment at Blue Origin must be a U.S. citizen or national, U.S. permanent resident (i.e. current Green Card holder), or lawfully admitted into the U.S. as a refugee or granted asylum.
Benefits
Benefits include: Medical, dental, vision, basic and supplemental life insurance, paid parental leave, short and long-term disability, 401(k) with a company match of up to 5%, and an Education Support Program.
Paid Time Off: Up to four (4) weeks per year based on weekly scheduled hours, and up to 14 company-paid holidays.
Discretionary bonus: Bonuses are designed to reward individual contributions as well as allow employees to share in company results.
Eligibility for benefits varies by role type, please check with your recruiter for a comprehensive list of the benefits available for this role.
Equal Employment Opportunity
Blue Origin is proud to be an Equal Opportunity/Affirmative Action Employer and is committed to attracting, retaining, and developing a highly qualified, diverse, and dedicated work force. Blue Origin hires and promotes people on the basis of their qualifications, performance, and abilities. We support the establishment and maintenance of a workplace that fosters trust, equality, and teamwork, in which all employees recognize and appreciate the diversity of individual team members. We provide all qualified applicants for employment and employees with equal opportunities for hire, promotion, and other terms and conditions of employment, regardless of their race, color, religion, gender, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin/ethnicity, age, physical or mental disability, genetic factors, military/veteran status, or any other status or characteristic protected by federal, state, and/or local law. DataAnnotation is committed to creating quality AI. Join our team to help train AI chatbots while gaining the flexibility of remote work and choosing your own schedule.
We are looking for a proficient Frontend Developer to join our team to train our AI chatbots to code. You will work with the chatbots that we are building in order to measure their progress, as well as write and evaluate code.
In this role you will need to be proficient in at least one programming language (Python, JavaScript, HTML, C++, C# and SQL) and able to solve coding problems (think LeetCode, HackerRank, etc). For each coding problem, you must be able to explain how your solution solves the problem.

Who we are:

For over 20 years, Global Relay has set the standard in enterprise information archiving with industry-leading cloud archiving, surveillance, eDiscovery, and analytics solutions. We securely capture and preserve the communications data of the world’s most highly regulated firms, giving them greater visibility and control over their information and ensuring compliance with stringent regulations.

Though we offer competitive compensation and benefits and all the other perks one would expect from an established company, we are not your typical technology company. Global Relay is a career-building company. A place for big ideas. New challenges. Groundbreaking innovation. It’s a place where you can genuinely make an impact – and be recognized for it.

We believe great businesses thrive on diversity, inclusion, and the contributions of all employees. To that end, we recruit candidates from different backgrounds and foster a work environment that encourages employees to collaborate and learn from each other, completely free of barriers.

We encourage you to apply if your qualifications and experience are a good fit for any of our openings.

Your role:

Global Relay is seeking a Director, Information Security to act as the organization’s trusted security resource. You will work closely with a variety of stakeholders including our commercial teams, Development and Engineering teams, and Operations team on all security-related matters.

Reporting to the Chief Information Security Officer (CISO), you will play a key role in ensuring the successful implementation and completion of security initiatives alongside Global Relay’s business objectives. You will be Global Relay’s expert in its security practices and provide guidance on ever evolving security challenges and convey our Information Security strategy to our global customers and employees with confidence. You will lead a diverse, global team of security professionals to ensure Global Relay can scale its security program along with its expected growth.

Your job:


Work with the CISO to provide senior level direction for our overall security programConstantly reinforce the security-minded culture of Global Relay to ensure it is the first and foremost focus across the business while working closely with the Heads of IT, Product Development, and Engineering to ensure constant alignment of the roadmapFoster a culture of security across Global Relay through staff training, documentation, and enforcing accountability at all levelsDevelop and execute strategic security programs that align with company goals and protect Global Relay’s information assetsManage a growing team, mentor and guide the development of the Cyber Security team to support career growthProvide regular reports with senior stakeholders on Global Relay’s cyber security standing, identified risks, and mitigation strategiesProvide initiative, direction, and project management to staff in support of our key security goals and objectives and be able to solve the problems encountered in a collaborative fashionAct as a liaison between the security team, senior stakeholders, and customersBe the main point of contact for various security audits and customer audits (ISO 27001, SOC2, Penetration testing, customer audits, etc.)Drive ISO 27001 practices for Global Relay’s ISMS and look for constant areas of improvementMaintain alignment with security industry standards through successful ISO 27001 and SOC 2 audit outcomesConstantly conduct evaluations of Global Relay’s security measures, identify vulnerabilities, and make recommendations to reduce risk in a cycle of continuous improvementPerform risk assessment reviews and see all security requirements through to completion related to key acquisitions of software and/or services as a part of the Global Relay Vendor Success (procurement) processSupervise all incident response planning and investigations of non-compliance, if any; Global Relay advertises the pay range for this role in accordance with the pay transparency laws of the state of New York. In addition to the annual base salary (range listed below), compensation for this role also includes a corporate bonus, extended health benefits, and 401k contributions, and (for applicable Sales roles) an enticing commission structure.

New York - Base Salary Range:

$120,000—$180,000 USD

What you can expect:

At Global Relay, there’s no ceiling to what you can achieve. It’s the land of opportunity for the energetic, the intelligent, the driven. You’ll receive the mentoring, coaching, and support you need to reach your career goals. You’ll be part of a culture that breeds creativity and rewards perseverance and hard work. And you’ll be working alongside smart, talented individuals from diverse backgrounds, with complementary knowledge and skills.

Global Relay is an equal-opportunity employer committed to diversity, equity, and inclusion.

We seek to ensure reasonable adjustments, accommodations, and personal time are tailored to meet the unique needs of every individual.

Job Description

What if you could use your technology skills to develop a product that impacts the way communities’ hospitals, homes, sports stadiums, and schools across the world are built? Construction impacts the lives of nearly everyone in the world, and yet it’s also one of the world’s least digitized industries, not to mention one of the most dangerous.

That’s why we’re looking for an experienced Senior Software Engineer, Backend to join Procore’s journey to revolutionize a historically underserved industry. In this role, you’ll join our highly collaborative Product and Engineering organization to drive the technical direction of our projects; specifically the Custom Field team, which allows our customers to define their project related data.

This position will report into the Senior Engineering Manager and will be based in our Austin location. We’re looking for someone to join our team immediately.

Fieldsets and Custom Fields are pivotal features in standardizing flexible data collection for Procore. Fieldsets allow clients to designate fields as required, optional, or hidden, while Custom Fields provide essential new data based on desired information types. Since 2019, these flexibility solutions have been added into 20+ tools, and are a crucial step for successful Procore client onboarding and implementation. The team is currently working on a re-architecture plan that will focus on enterprise customers and bring unified and consistent experiences to the broader Procore ecosystem.

What you'll do:

Collaborate with Engineering, Product, and UX to design and build solutions that delight users and solve critical business problemsServe as a leader and mentor to more junior engineers within your teamWork up and down the stack to ship code for our Rails backend and our React frontend, and dive deep into the database layer to handle complex querying needsWrite, design, and execute automated tests by creating scripts that run testing functions automatically

What we're looking for: 

5+ years experience in Object-Oriented Program fundamentals, Test Driven Development and Design principles (Ruby on Rails, Python, Java)Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science, a related field, or comparable work experienceTrack record of anticipating technical problems that will fall out of major projects and designing solutions to overcome those problemsExperience designing and building software in a Service-Oriented ArchitectureStrong experience documenting and bringing team clarity to complex solutionsTime-honed expertise with modern web development across the entire spectrum of development, testing, staging, deploying, and monitoringA curious mind that is driven to innovate and solve customer problems

Additional Information

Base Pay Range $134,800 - $185,350. Eligible for Equity Compensation. Procore is committed to offering competitive, fair, and commensurate compensation, and has provided an estimated pay range for this role. Actual compensation will be based on a candidate’s job-related skills, experience, education or training, and location.

Perks & Benefits

At Procore, we invest in our employees and provide a full range of benefits and perks to help you grow and thrive. From generous paid time off and healthcare coverage to career enrichment and development programs, learn more details about what we offer and how we empower you to be your best.

About Us

Procore Technologies is building the software that builds the world. We provide cloud-based construction management software that helps clients more efficiently build skyscrapers, hospitals, retail centers, airports, housing complexes, and more. At Procore, we have worked hard to create and maintain a culture where you can own your work and are encouraged and given resources to try new ideas. Check us out on Glassdoor to see what others are saying about working at Procore.

We are an equal-opportunity employer and welcome builders of all backgrounds. We thrive in a diverse, dynamic, and inclusive environment. We do not tolerate discrimination against employees on the basis of age, color, disability, gender, gender identity or expression, marital status, national origin, political affiliation, race, religion, sexual orientation, veteran status, or any other classification protected by law.

If you'd like to stay in touch and be the first to hear about new roles at Procore, join our Talent Community.

As a Principal Engineer, you will play a crucial role in setting technical direction, providing technical leadership, and ensuring the successful delivery of complex projects. You will work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to drive the development of cutting-edge technologies, mentor engineers, and contribute to our company's technical vision and strategy.

You will need to anticipate potential obstacles and manage escalations. There will be no perfect decision, requiring making tradeoffs and balancing business needs with technical constraints to arrive at the best solution. You are expected to possess the ability to break down large and complex projects into manageable tasks, create functional specifications, and ensure their successful and timely completion. The ideal candidate can differentiate between important and urgent matters, identify the best way forward from various scenarios, and gain the trust of stakeholders and end users.

In This Role, You Will

Foster a culture of technical excellence and innovation, driving continuous improvement initiatives and promoting the adoption of emerging technologies.Lead and manage the technical delivery of enterprise-level infrastructure projects, ensuring adherence to architectural design principals, security standards, and project timelines.Provide technical guidance and mentorship to cross-functional teams, ensuring alignment with project goals and objectives.Develop and maintain strong relationships with key stakeholders, acting as the primary technical point of contact for project-related communications and escalations.

Required:

7+ years of engineering experience, or equivalent demonstrated through one or a combination of the following: work experience, training, military experience, education7+ years of enterprise infrastructure technologies, including virtualization, networking, storage, and security.7+ years with Infrastructure as Code and Configuration Management tools (Puppet, Ansible, Terraform, Chef, Salt)7+ years experience public cloud (Azure/GCP) with hands-on experience in deploying and managing applications in the cloud.

Desired:

3+ years Docker, Kubernetes and PCF. Managing high availability and efficient deployment of cloud-native applications.7+ years of delivery experience with a proven track record of success7+ skills in automation, scripting, and infrastructure as code.Expertise in designing complex, distributed, and scalable enterprise level applications.Hands on experience creating and managing automated OS image builds with tools such as Packr or Image Builder.Strong expertise in VMWare HCX and ESXi for efficient workload migration across different environmentsFamiliarity with monitoring and logging tools, such as Prometheus, Grafana, ELK Stack, etc.Experience with GitOps principles and tools, such as Git, Flux, or ArgoCD, for managing infrastructure and application deployments.Proficiency in API gateways, such as Kong or Apigee, for managing and securing APIs.Knowledge of Service Mesh technologies, such as Istio, Linkerd, or Consul, for microservices communication and observability.

Job Expectations:

This position requires working in a hybrid environmentThere is no visa sponsorship available for this position.
